Flask and  MySQL Docker Networking

##  Overview
      This project demonstrates Docker networking using two separate containers:
          - Flask application (backend)
          - MySQL database

##  Architecture
      Flask container connects to MySQL container using Docker network.

##  Steps to Run

Step 1. Create Docker network
          docker network create mynetwork

Step 2. Run MySQL container
          docker run -d \
          --name mysql \
          --network mynetwork \
          -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root \
          -e MYSQL_DATABASE=mydb \
          mysql:5.7

Step 3. Build Flask image
docker build -t flaskapp .

Step 4. Run Flask container
docker run -d \
--name flaskapp \
--network mynetwork \
-p 5000:5000 \
flaskapp

Step 5. Access application
http://localhost:5000
